(381, '2010-05-14', 99, 1294, 'Avon, The women''s company is a company of women''sproducts which are according to ma research represented in 145 countries all over the world.\r\nI understand this position as a position of benefiting Avon as a company by performing the following duties:\r\n1 .  Reaching sales and \r\nprofit contribution performance objectives of the district. \r\n 2 .  Implementing the district strategies to achieve the sales and/or profit objectives while maximising penetration of targeted consumer segments. \r\n 3 .  Implementing business plans and key objectives to achieve financial returns. \r\n 4 .  Effectively managing the districts Representatives and Co-ordinators, and therefore ensuring the districts customers are serviced appropriately. \r\n 5 .  Ensuring that existing resources (human and financial) are managed appropriately to optimise performance within the district. \r\n 6 .  Conducting one planning day per campaign, which focuses on identifying and scheduling and appropriate plans/tactics, targeted to achieve objectives as agreed upon with the Division Sales Manager. \r\n 7 .  Contributing to the Companys success by developing a competitive awareness within the district and among the districts Co-ordinators and Representative and reporting competitive activity. \r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Tabitha N. Ngotipeni\r\nPO Box 23204\r\nWindhoek\r\nNamibia\r\n\r\n14 May 2010\r\n\r\nThe HR Department\r\nAvon\r\n\r\nDear Sir/Madam\r\n\r\nApplication for Vacant: District sales manager\r\n\r\nI am Tabitha Ngotipeni currently enrolling toward my Bachelor of Human Resources Management at polytechnic of Namibia. I hereby would like to apply for vacant: District sales manager advertised on Namrecruit website. I believe that my credentials and interests match with your requirements, hence I would like to submit my application.\r\n\r\nI have a comprehensive knowledge in computer skills, (word, outlook, excel, database, access, PowerPoint and ICT), good command in communication skills, report writing, interpersonal skills, I  also perceive myself to be a suitable candidates as I am equipped with extensive knowledge of general Human resources and Administration practices, procedures and principles. I am optimistic with my individual attributes, results oriented work driven ethics, a solid educational background. And I am prepared to make a significant contribution to the overall performance of Avon in general once Im given an opportunity.\r\n\r\nIm intense to develop myself and would like to contribute my skills and abilities to an institution that is innovative, growing and developing to a high standard like Avon. Attached, are my detailed CV and, testimonials and qualifications.\r\n\r\nI will be grateful if my application receives your favorable consideration.\r\n\r\nYours Faithfully\r\n\r\n\r\nTabitha N. Ngotipeni\r\n', 62.5, 0, 31.25, 1, 0, 0, 0),
