(1220, '2010-10-13', 184, 1294, 'As Im currently studying towards Bachelor of Human Resources Management in possession of a National Diploma in Human Resources Management, I believe my qualifications plus the knowledge that I have aquired during my studies and thorough the Student Exchange Programme that I have undergone between the Polytechnic of Namibia and FH Kufstein in Austria matches with the requirements of this position and they makes me a qualified candidate to apply for this post.', 'I do as much as I can, ikn terms of being employed in a certain organisation, I will do everything possible to do my work effectively and efficiently, I will do my work to meet my due dates, I will  do my work in time to avoid being on pressure while I had time to do my work. Everything an employee is suppose to, suppose to be enligned with the company''s and departmental objectives, to improve the company''s productivity and provide job satisfaction for themselves.', 'Duties and responsibility of HR Officer:\r\noPersonnel Management\r\noPayroll Administration\r\noOccupational Wellness and Safety\r\noManage the Administration affairs of the company including all the programmes and projects run or supported by the company if there is any\r\noMaintain and update all important company data such as property procurement, lease contracts and building plans\r\noPetty cash administration\r\noFilling\r\n', 'A market related remuneration such N$60 000- N$100 000 per annum', 'Management depends from one organisation to another and every organisation has its own policies and regurations, therefore one is not suppose to choose on how they suppose to be managed as long as the management is following policies, rules and regulations in the company such person is working.', 'Tabitha N. Ngotipeni\r\nPO Box 23204\r\nWindhoek\r\nNamibia\r\n\r\n13 October 2010 \r\n\r\nThe Human Resources Department\r\nHR@work Recruitment Consultancy\r\nWindhoek\r\n\r\nDear Sir/Madam\r\n\r\nApplication for Human Resources Officer  \r\n\r\nI am Tabitha Ngotipeni currently enrolling toward my Bachelor of Human Resources Management at polytechnic of Namibia, to be completed on 17th November 2010 and currently unemployed. I hereby would like to apply for vacant: Human Resources Officer, advertised on hr@work website 2010 or any other job related to human resources management which may be available in your company. I believe that my qualifications, capability and interests match with your requirements, hence I would like to submit my application.\r\n\r\nI have a comprehensive knowledge in computer skills, (word, outlook, excel, database, access, PowerPoint and ICT), good command in communication skills, report writing, interpersonal skills, I  also perceive myself to be a suitable candidate as I am equipped with extensive knowledge of general Human resources and Administration practices, procedures and principles. I am optimistic with my individual attributes, results oriented work driven ethics, a solid educational background. And I am prepared to make a significant contribution to the overall performance of your organisation once Im given an opportunity.\r\n\r\nIm intense to develop myself and would like to contribute my skills and abilities to an institution that is innovative, growing and developing. Attached, are my detailed CV, testimonials and qualifications and other related documents.\r\n\r\nI will be grateful if my application receives your favorable consideration.\r\n\r\nYours Faithfully\r\n\r\n\r\nTabitha N. Ngotipeni\r\n\r\n', 50, 0, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0),
