(1442, '2010-11-01', 200, 3554, 'I provided excellent customer service when I was debt and customer relations manager at Aupie Agro Limited(a hire purchase of domestic goods service provider company in Lusaka, Zambia) from the year 2005 to 2007. Apart from planning, directing, controlling and implementing the debt collection function of the company, I was also in charge of smoothing our relations with our customers and other stakeholders. My team and I solved customer complaints due to billing, delivery and identity issues. We made follow-ups on from our customers after they collected goods to find out how the goods were working and also to offer new sales services when new stocks of goods arrived. \r\n\r\nI sourced new customers by following up on old sales and looked for new customers at the same time. The methods of advertising used were often in the form of phone calls, writing, word of mouth and mobile sales. \r\n\r\nAs a result of proving excellent customers service, the sales base improved and collections increased. \r\n\r\nApart from providing excellent customer services, I also enjoyed my work.', 'My strongest characteristics are being able to adapt to new conditions and environment by being humble and having a spirit for helping other people.\r\nI am not afraid of taking risks, I can multi-task and work well under pressure.\r\nI am also deadline-driven and I am also a strong team player with excellent interpersonal and negotiation skills.\r\nI have the experience of supervising staff and an understanding of the issues involved in staff supervision. \r\nI have the ability and experience of producing statutory accounts and other financial information to suit different audiences. \r\nFinally and not the least, I have formal accounting and human resources management qualifications, excellent computer skills, strong understanding of equal opportunities, cultural diversity and gender issues as well as a commitment to apply relevant policies accordingly. ', '', '