(2391, '2011-05-09', 313, 6732, '', '', '', '', '', 'Re: Application for the post of Farm Services/ Maintenance Manager\r\nDear Sir/Madam\r\nI am a Group Operations Manager with more than six years of experience in the field of agricultural production (Farming) and have requisite experience in personnel training and supervision, production management and planning, stock control and procurement procedures. I have a 3 year Bachelors degree in Agriculture and Natural resource Management majoring in Agribusiness management. I also possess the requisite experience in poultry production and have my own poultry production project (Broilers) based in Zimbabwe.I am a perfect match for the position you advertised in Namibian on Monday the 9th of May 2011.\r\nHere is a description of how my experience compares with your requirements.\r\nJob requirements	My experience\r\nManagement of general farm and chicken houses maintenance.	Section Manager at ARDA Chisumbanje Estate\r\nSupervise project personnel, human resources, training provision	Human resource training, control and development at Chisumbanje, ZFU, CRS, Agribank and current position.\r\nPlanning and Implementation of standard operating procedures.	Production planning at Chisumbanje, development of Operational strategies for small scale farmers, Imlementation of Livestock and Poultry re-stocking program at ZFU\r\n\r\nI believe that the experience gained in my current position has given me exposure to Namibia that gives me insight into th agricultural sector in Namibia and especially in the Livestock and related sectors through various projects including development of feedlots in Grootfontein and assisting a number of individuals in establishing small scale poultry production projects in Northern Namibia.\r\nI would welcome the opportunity to further discuss my skills and this position. If you have questions or would like to schedule an interview, please contact me by phone at 0814 731 575 or by e-mail at kingerry2000@ya