(2537, '2011-05-16', 322, 1558, 'I Adam Siteketa, hold a Bachelors Degree in Economics from the University of Namibia having graduated in 1998. since then I have gathered  extensive experience in the fields of planning and development as well as finances after  working in the Ministry of Finance (as a Senior Taxation Officer); at National Planning Commission (as an Economist  Budgeting) and was also seconded to work with the 2001 Population and Housing Census as a Regional Supervisor based in the Kunene Region. Later-on I transferred to the Kavango Regional Council (as a Regional Economic Planner). My work therefore was of working with statistics and data analysis and this field had been always at heart with me and thus am now currently doing a  2nd degree course at UNAM majoring in Accounting and Business Statistics.', 'I have worked with different sectors in all the 13 regions of Namibia in different economic and developmental activities and would therefore install the good working relationship as before. My experiences stretch across working with the grassroots in terms of training them in different areas of development in order for them to identify their own developmental needs or gaps. I worked as a secretariat to the Regional Development coordinating Committee (RDCC), as a member of the Regional Emergency Management Unit ( REMU), a secretariat of the Regional Tender Board, as a member of the Technical Committee for Food/Cash For-Work Projects, worked as a team member and coordinator for the compilation of the Regional Development Plans (RDPs) and National Development Plans (NDPs), was a member of the Settlement Committees and Build Together Committees and also worked hand-in-hand with different consultants in the areas of planning, surveying, servicing and construction of capital projects in the region. \r\n\r\nI have theoretical skills in consumer behaviour having done Research Methodology and Marketing in my field of study in Industrial Psychology and Macro 