(2680, '2011-06-16', 344, 7035, 'At a previous job where I had to create an employee filling system for over 200 empoyees as the company had no filling system. Also monthly payroll processing which I do with minimum fault every month. Also had a record for wage negotiations in the least number of days when compared to previous years.', 'No. Just as long as you have all your facts you can easily make a desicion based on these facts.', 'At a previous employer where, as the HR Administrator, I had to inform team members who were employed by the factory for many many years that a new Performance Management system was going to be implemented. I had to explain the whole process to the m in lay-man''s language as most of our team members wer uneducated and I had to make sure that the whole transition was as smooth as possible. It took time and patience to explain everything and the whole process of KPI''s and achieving targets and the employee rewards attached to the new process. At the end all went well and the agreement between all employees and management was signed peacefully. I met my objective by getting our team members to agree to this new system of reward and recognition.', 'At university. During final year our Industrial Psychology consisted of powerpoint presentations all year long, we students worked in teams. At times it was difficult to get all team members to cooperate but as part of the team leader committee I used the strategy of always reminding them about our aim and objectives that we''d like to meet and that it was only going to be through commitment that we''d be able to meet these. through using this strategy we managed to always meet the common goal shared.', 'At my current company. As an HR Officer, I am only doing Payroll. Human Resources is such a broad field and I would like to be involved in a lot of these fields (as your Job Description above). Doing only Payroll really frustrates me because during the rest of the month it gets pretty quiet. I